<subSubSection pageNumber="291" type="multiple">
<paragraph pageNumber="291">
Although 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Kerguélen">Kerguelen</normalizedToken>
(in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="291">Lejeunia</emphasis>
, n.s., 75: 196. 1975) stated &quot;Type: 
<normalizedToken originalValue="…LINN”">...LINN&quot;</normalizedToken>
, this is not accepted as a formal typification, for the reasons explained by Cafferty &amp; al. (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="291">Taxon</emphasis>
49: 240. 2000). Romero Zarco (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="291">Lagascalia</emphasis>
14: 122. 1986) subsequently chose 1211.15 (LINN) as 
<typeStatus>lectotype</typeStatus>
but 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Clayton’s">Clayton's</normalizedToken>
choice has priority. See 
<normalizedToken originalValue="López">Lopez</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken originalValue="González">Gonzalez</normalizedToken>
(in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="291">Anales Jard. Bot. Madrid</emphasis>
51: 313. 1993), who discusses various aspects of the typification of this name.
</paragraph>
